          "distinct": true,
          "id": "d410ac3d3a87ea36990e5f647c90e569e1e98b90",
          "message": "fix: restrict LTO flags to C++ sources only (fixes audit CI) (#120)\n\nThe -flto=thin (Clang) and -flto (GCC) flags were applied via\ntarget_compile_options(PRIVATE) to ALL sources including .S assembly.\nOn CI, CMake invokes the system cc (GCC) for .S files, which does not\nunderstand -flto=thin, causing 'unrecognized argument' errors.\n\nFix: use $<COMPILE_LANGUAGE:CXX> generator expression so LTO flags\nonly apply to C++ compilation units. Assembly files already have\n-fno-lto in their per-file COMPILE_FLAGS as a safety net.\n\nAlso bumps VERSION.txt to 3.21.0.\n\nCo-authored-by: shrec <shrec@users.noreply.github.com>",
          "timestamp": "2026-03-08T21:55:52+04:00",
          "tree_id": "d693859a1cb4d9fc33f063edb512c419dfd13d2b",
          "url": "https://github.com/shrec/UltrafastSecp256k1/commit/d410ac3d3a87ea36990e5f647c90e569e1e98b90"
